Forecasting Credit Default

Thu Nguyen

9/30/2020

For this project I would like to dive into three points: 1/ What are relationships of each categories with the bank’s approval decision? 2/ How those categories effect the loan’s default risk? 3/ I also want to predict the risk of loans being default based on the past loan data.

The Data

For this project, I will use the loan data available from Lending Club’s website (https://www.lendingclub.com/statistics/additional-statistics?). LendingClub is a US peer-to-peer lending company which matches borrowers with investors willing to fund their loans. The data files contain complete loan data for all loans issued from quater 2 of 2018 to Q1 2020. The data is a matrix of over 1 million observations and 150 variables. It contains variables such as loan amount, interest rate, credit score, the current loan status (Current, Late, Fully Paid, etc.), latest payment information and so on. The name of the data file is Loans

Part 4 (Reflection)

1/ What was the most difficult portion of this project?

The most difficult portion of this project was to identify the topic for the project. I realized that there are two main points we should consider when choosing the topic. First, we need to be interested in the topic. Second, we should choose the topic that have good amount of data that we can get. I wasted a lot of my time on choosing the topic. At first, i wanted to analyze AliExpress data since i was interested to open an online store, so i thought this project could help me to find out what would be hot products to see. However, AliExpress does not have good amount of data for me to get. Thus, after couple days trying to scape the data from AliExpress website, i gave up. I changed it to analyze the Lending Club data. The data is so easy to get from Lending Club website with good amount of information. Also i have little knowledge on the finance area, so it was easier for me to understand the data.

2/ What influenced your choice of research question?

I worked at the bank before and always curious how the bank decide who they would approve and who they would decline for a loan. I also hope i could get a job as a data analyst at the bank later, so this project could be helpful for me later to show to my future employer. Therefore, i want to know more about what drive their decision and what i can contribute to provide them better information for better decision.

3/ Did you take advantage of the student worksessions? How did those help?

Even though i have not participated in discussion during class, i learned by listen to other students. There are students with questions every class, so i learn about their problems which they encounter with their project, what mistake they made with their codes and so on. Those help me to have an idea of what i should or should not do.

4/ Think about where you were when you started this course, at each project milestone, and now. What are you most proud of in your progress? What regrets do you have?

I think the best think i learn from this course is how to encounter a problem, how to ask the right questions and where to search for the answers. I know i was not able to learn as much as other students in this class and I am not strong on technical skills at this point yet but I am still proud of myself for what i have been able to do. At least i can look at the code and understand what the code gonna do instead of feeling dizzy like before. I dont have any regret at this point. My result, my skill might not improve a lot but i know i did my best. I have worked very hard and able to finish this program even with a full time job and 2 little kids.
